        name: "News Website",
        description:
          "News websites demand split-second load times, real-time content delivery, and layouts that keep readers consuming story after story. EDMA builds high-performance news website designs for media houses, digital publishers, and news portals across Indore, India, and international markets. From regional Hindi-language news portals targeting Madhya Pradesh audiences to English-language global news platforms, we engineer media websites built for traffic and revenue.\n\nWhy News Website Design Matters: In 2024, 82% of news readers access content via mobile devices — meaning mobile performance is your most critical technical factor. News websites that achieve Google News inclusion receive 3–5x more organic traffic than those that don't. Sub-1-second load times are the difference between retaining readers and watching them bounce to competitors. Additionally, strategic ad placement architecture can increase advertising revenue by 40–80% compared to generic layouts.\n\nOur Approach at EDMA (Indore & Global): Our news website designs feature dynamic homepage layouts with breaking news tickers, category-based navigation, and trending story sections that maximize page views per session. We implement AMP (Accelerated Mobile Pages) for Google News eligibility and mobile performance. Ad placement is architecturally integrated — maximizing CPM revenue without destroying UX. Our news websites handle thousands of articles, millions of monthly visitors, and peak traffic surges during breaking events.\n\nKey Benefits: Real-Time Content Delivery with live update architecture; Google News Eligible with AMP and news schema markup; High Ad Revenue Layout with strategic monetization placement; Breaking News Ready with scalable infrastructure. Built for Indore regional publishers, India-wide media companies, and international news organizations.\n\nFAQ: Can EDMA build a news website in Hindi and English? Yes — we build fully bilingual and multilingual news websites with separate content management for each language. What CMS do you use for news websites? We recommend WordPress with specialized news themes, custom-built CMS solutions, or Drupal for enterprise-scale publishers.",
