    id: "web-dev",
    title: "Website Development",
    color: "#84cc16",
    gradient: "from-lime-400 to-green-400",
    glow: "#84cc16",
    AnimComp: WebDevAnim,
    subcategories: [
      {
        name: "Front-End Development",
        description:
          "Front-End Development is the art and science of creating everything a user sees and interacts with on a website or web application. At EDMA — one of the top front-end development agencies in Indore, India — we craft pixel-perfect, blazing-fast user interfaces that captivate visitors and convert them into loyal customers. Our front-end engineers are experts in React, Vue.js, Angular, Next.js, HTML5, CSS3, and modern JavaScript (ES2023+), ensuring your digital product looks stunning on every device and browser.\n\nWhy Front-End Development Matters: The front end is your brand's first impression. Studies show that 94% of first impressions are design-related, and 88% of online consumers are less likely to return after a bad experience. A fast, accessible, and visually impressive front end directly improves your SEO rankings, bounce rate, and conversion rate.\n\nOur Approach at EDMA (Indore & Global): We start with a thorough UX audit and wireframe review, then build reusable component libraries that scale effortlessly. We implement lazy loading, code splitting, tree shaking, and critical CSS inlining to achieve sub-2-second load times. Every interface we build meets WCAG 2.1 accessibility standards and is tested across Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge on desktop and mobile.\n\nKey Benefits: Performance-first architecture using Core Web Vitals best practices; responsive design from 320px mobile to 4K displays; SEO-friendly semantic HTML structure; cross-browser and cross-device testing. Serving clients across Indore, Mumbai, Delhi, Bangalore, and internationally in the USA, UK, Australia, and UAE.\n\nFAQ: How long does front-end development take? A standard front-end project takes 4–8 weeks depending on complexity. Simple landing pages can be delivered in 1–2 weeks.",
        benefits: [
          "React & Vue",
          "Core Web Vitals",
          "Cross-Browser",
          "WCAG Accessible",
        ],
      },
      {
        name: "Back-End Development",
        description:
          "Back-End Development is the engine powering every successful web application — the databases, servers, APIs, and business logic making your platform work reliably at scale. EDMA's back-end development team in Indore, India builds rock-solid server-side systems using Node.js, Python (Django/FastAPI), PHP (Laravel), Ruby on Rails, and Java Spring Boot, serving clients globally across the USA, UK, Canada, and Australia.\n\nWhat We Build: Our engineers design and implement RESTful APIs, GraphQL endpoints, microservices architectures, authentication systems, payment processing pipelines, real-time WebSocket servers, and high-performance database schemas optimized for your exact workload.\n\nDatabase Expertise: We work with PostgreSQL, MySQL, MongoDB, Redis, Elasticsearch, and cloud-native databases like AWS Aurora and Firebase. Our architects design indexing strategies, caching layers, and sharding configurations keeping your application fast under millions of concurrent users.\n\nSecurity-First Development: Every system we build follows OWASP Top 10 security guidelines. We implement JWT/OAuth2 authentication, rate limiting, SQL injection prevention, input sanitization, and encrypted data storage as standard practice.\n\nScalability & DevOps: We design for horizontal scaling from day one. Containerization with Docker, CI/CD pipelines with GitHub Actions, and cloud deployment on AWS/GCP/Azure are all part of our standard delivery. Servicing businesses in Indore, across India, and globally with 24/7 monitoring and support plans.\n\nFAQ: What back-end technology is best for my project? It depends on your use case — Node.js for real-time apps, Python for data-heavy applications, Laravel for rapid development. We recommend the right stack during our free consultation call.",
        benefits: [
          "Node.js & Python",
          "API Architecture",
          "OWASP Security",
          "Cloud Scalable",
        ],
      },
      {
        name: "Full-Stack Development",
        description:
          "Full-Stack Development means owning the entire technology stack — from the database to the user interface — under one cohesive, expertly coordinated team. EDMA is a premier full-stack development company based in Indore, India, delivering end-to-end web solutions to startups, SMEs, and enterprises across the globe, including the USA, UK, Canada, Singapore, and the UAE.\n\nWhat Full-Stack Development Includes: Our engineers handle front-end UI (React, Next.js, Vue), back-end APIs (Node.js, Django, Laravel), database design (PostgreSQL, MongoDB), cloud infrastructure (AWS, GCP), CI/CD pipelines, authentication systems, and third-party integrations — everything needed to launch and scale your product.\n\nWhy Choose EDMA: Coordinating separate front-end and back-end teams is expensive and introduces miscommunication risks. Our full-stack approach eliminates handoff friction, accelerates delivery timelines by 40%, and ensures architectural decisions are made holistically.\n\nTech Stacks We Excel In: MERN (MongoDB, Express, React, Node), MEAN (Angular), PERN (PostgreSQL), Django + React, Laravel + Vue, and Next.js full-stack with serverless functions. We match the stack to your performance, scalability, and budget requirements.\n\nOur full-stack projects include SaaS platforms, marketplace applications, enterprise dashboards, EdTech platforms, FinTech solutions, and healthcare portals. Serving Indore, Bhopal, Pune, Hyderabad, and international clients with end-to-end ownership and transparent project management.\n\nFAQ: Is full-stack development more expensive than hiring separate teams? No — it is typically 30–50% more cost-effective due to eliminated coordination overhead, faster delivery, and a single point of accountability.",
        benefits: [
