      {
        name: "Progressive Web App (PWA) Development",
        description:
          "Progressive Web App (PWA) Development delivers the best of both worlds — the reach of the web combined with the experience of a native mobile app — without the cost and complexity of App Store publishing. EDMA is a specialized PWA development company in Indore, India, building installable, offline-capable web applications for global clients looking to maximize reach and minimize development cost.\n\nWhat Makes PWAs Powerful: PWAs can be installed on Android and iOS home screens directly from the browser — no App Store required. They work offline or on slow connections using intelligent caching via Service Workers. They send push notifications, access device hardware like cameras and GPS, and load instantly thanks to aggressive caching strategies.\n\nBusiness Case for PWAs: App Store submissions face rejection risks, 30% revenue cuts on in-app purchases, and 2–3 week review delays. PWAs bypass all of this. Brands like Twitter, Pinterest, and Starbucks have deployed PWAs with reported 2–4x improvements in conversion rates and 5x reductions in data usage.\n\nWhat We Build: Full PWA architecture with Web App Manifest, Service Worker lifecycle management, push notification systems, offline data synchronization using IndexedDB, background sync, and app shell architecture for instant loading. We also convert existing websites into PWAs.\n\nTechnologies: React with Workbox, Next.js PWA plugin, Vue PWA setup, and custom Service Worker implementations. Serving startups and enterprises in Indore, across India, and globally.\n\nFAQ: Can a PWA really replace a native app? For most use cases — yes. PWAs now support camera, GPS, push notifications, offline mode, and home screen installation on both Android and iOS.",
