        name: "Cloud-Based Web Development",
        description:
          "Cloud-Based Web Development architects your web application on cloud infrastructure from day one — enabling elastic scaling, global availability, automated backups, and cost efficiency that traditional server hosting simply cannot match. EDMA is a certified cloud development partner in Indore, India, building AWS, Google Cloud Platform, and Microsoft Azure-based solutions for startups and enterprises worldwide.\n\nWhy Cloud-Native Matters: Cloud-native applications scale automatically with demand — no manual server provisioning, no traffic-related downtime. During product launches or viral traffic events, your application automatically spins up additional capacity and scales back down when demand drops, charging you only for what you use.\n\nCloud Services We Architect With: AWS EC2/ECS/Lambda for compute; RDS/DynamoDB/Aurora for databases; S3/CloudFront for storage and CDN; SQS/SNS for messaging; ElastiCache (Redis) for caching; CloudFormation/Terraform for infrastructure as code. On GCP: Cloud Run, Firestore, BigQuery. On Azure: App Service, Cosmos DB, Azure Functions.\n\nCost Optimization: We implement auto-scaling policies, reserved instance purchasing, spot instance usage for batch jobs, and right-sizing recommendations that typically reduce cloud bills by 30–50% compared to over-provisioned static servers.\n\nDevOps Integration: All cloud projects include CI/CD pipelines, infrastructure as code (IaC), environment parity between dev/staging/production, automated testing gates, and deployment rollback capabilities. Serving cloud-first startups and enterprise IT departments across Indore, India, and globally.\n\nFAQ: Is cloud hosting more expensive than traditional hosting? Initially, per-unit costs may seem higher, but elimination of over-provisioning and operational overhead makes cloud 40–60% more cost-effective at scale.",
