      {
        name: "Website Optimization (Speed & Performance)",
        description:
          "Website Speed and Performance Optimization transforms slow, underperforming websites into lightning-fast digital experiences that rank higher on Google, retain visitors longer, and convert at significantly higher rates. EDMA is a dedicated web performance optimization agency based in Indore, India, achieving measurable Core Web Vitals improvements for clients across e-commerce, SaaS, media, and corporate sectors globally.\n\nThe Business Impact of Speed: Amazon found that every 100ms of latency costs 1% of revenue. Google research shows a 1-second delay in mobile page load reduces conversions by 20%. Our performance optimization directly impacts your bottom line, not just technical scores.\n\nWhat We Optimize: Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) — optimizing hero images, fonts, and render-blocking resources; First Input Delay (FID/INP) — removing main thread blocking JavaScript; Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) — fixing image dimensions and dynamic content insertion; Time to First Byte (TTFB) — server optimization, caching, and CDN configuration.\n\nOptimization Techniques We Apply: WebP/AVIF image conversion with responsive srcsets; critical CSS inlining and non-critical CSS deferral; JavaScript code splitting and tree shaking; font subsetting and preloading; CDN implementation (Cloudflare, AWS CloudFront); Redis/Varnish server-side caching; database query optimization; HTTP/3 enablement; third-party script auditing and lazy loading.\n\nMeasurable Results: Our typical engagement achieves Google PageSpeed scores of 90+ on both mobile and desktop. Serving businesses across Indore, India, and globally.\n\nFAQ: How long does performance optimization take? A comprehensive optimization audit and implementation takes 2–4 weeks. Emergency optimizations for critical sites can be completed in 3–5 business days.",
