      {
        name: "Headless CMS Development",
        description:
          "Headless CMS Development decouples your content management backend from your content delivery frontend — giving your editors a powerful, intuitive writing interface while your development team has complete freedom to deliver that content through any channel: websites, mobile apps, digital signage, smart TVs, voice assistants, or AR/VR experiences. EDMA is a headless CMS specialist based in Indore, India, building Jamstack and omnichannel content architectures for global brands.\n\nWhy Headless Is the Future of Content Management: Traditional CMS platforms like WordPress tightly couple content and presentation, making it painful to deliver content to multiple channels or redesign the front end without disrupting editorial workflows. Headless CMS liberates content, making it a structured, API-accessible asset that can be delivered anywhere.\n\nHeadless CMS Platforms We Work With: Contentful — enterprise-grade with powerful content modeling; Sanity — developer-friendly with real-time collaborative editing; Strapi — self-hosted, open-source, fully customizable; Directus — database-first with a powerful admin panel; Prismic — great for marketing teams; Storyblok — visual editor with component-based content.\n\nFront-End Delivery: We connect headless CMS to Next.js, Nuxt.js, Astro, Gatsby, or custom React/Vue front ends, implementing ISR (Incremental Static Regeneration) for instant content updates without full rebuilds.\n\nContent Modeling Expertise: Well-designed content models are the foundation of scalable headless architecture. We spend significant discovery time designing modular, reusable content types that grow with your business. Serving media companies, e-commerce brands, and enterprise marketing teams across Indore, India, and globally.\n\nFAQ: Is a headless CMS harder for non-technical editors to use? Modern headless CMS platforms like Sanity and Storyblok offer visual editors that are as user-friendly as WordPress — often more so.",
