        name: "Jamstack Development",
        description:
          "Jamstack Development is a modern web architecture philosophy that pre-builds as much as possible, serves from CDN, and enhances with APIs and serverless functions — delivering websites that are faster, more secure, and cheaper to operate than traditional server-rendered alternatives. EDMA is a Jamstack-specialized development team based in Indore, India, delivering high-performance Jamstack projects for marketing agencies, e-commerce brands, and SaaS products globally.\n\nThe Jamstack Philosophy: JavaScript running on the client for dynamic functionality; APIs accessed over HTTPS for server-side logic and database interactions; Markup pre-built at deploy time and served from CDN edge nodes globally.\n\nWhy Jamstack Outperforms Traditional Stacks: No server to hack — your site is static files on a CDN, eliminating 80% of the attack surface. No server to maintain — zero patch management, no server downtime. Sub-100ms TTFB globally — CDN edge nodes deliver files from the node nearest to each visitor worldwide.\n\nJamstack Tools We Use: Next.js and Nuxt.js for hybrid static/dynamic sites; Astro for content-heavy sites with zero JavaScript overhead; Gatsby for GraphQL-powered sites; Eleventy and Hugo for blazing-fast documentation and marketing sites; Netlify and Vercel for CI/CD and serverless function hosting; Cloudflare Pages for global edge deployment.\n\nJamstack plus E-commerce: Combining Jamstack with headless e-commerce (Shopify Hydrogen, CommerceJS, Medusa.js) delivers online stores with perfect PageSpeed scores and unmatched reliability. Serving clients across Indore, India, and globally.\n\nFAQ: Is Jamstack suitable for large websites with thousands of pages? Yes. With ISR (Incremental Static Regeneration) in Next.js, even million-page sites build and update efficiently.",
        benefits: [
          "CDN-Edge Global",
          "Zero Attack Surface",
          "PageSpeed 100",
          "Serverless Functions",
        ],
      },
