        name: "Social Media Marketing (SMM)",
        description:
          "Social Media Marketing (SMM) transforms social platforms into powerful business-growth engines. EDMA's social media team manages your presence across Facebook, Instagram, LinkedIn, Twitter/X, YouTube, and Pinterest — building engaged communities, increasing brand awareness, and driving measurable revenue through strategic organic and paid social campaigns.\n\nOur Social Media Services: Content creation and calendar management, community management, paid social advertising, influencer collaboration, social listening, competitor benchmarking, and monthly performance reporting. We handle everything end-to-end so your team can focus on running your business.\n\nPlatform-Specific Strategy: Each platform requires a different content approach. Instagram demands visual storytelling and Reels; LinkedIn requires thought leadership and professional content; Facebook excels at community building and targeted advertising; YouTube rewards long-form educational content and product demos. We craft platform-native strategies that resonate with each audience.\n\nContent That Converts: Our creative team produces scroll-stopping graphics, short-form videos, carousels, stories, and infographics that align with your brand identity. Every post is crafted with clear calls-to-action designed to move followers down your marketing funnel.\n\nPaid Social Advertising: We run sophisticated paid social campaigns using custom audiences, lookalike targeting, retargeting pixels, and behavioral segmentation to reach your ideal customers with precision. Our campaigns consistently achieve below-industry-average cost-per-result metrics.\n\nServing clients across Indore, India, and globally including the USA, UK, Singapore, and Australia.\n\nFAQ: How many posts per week do you publish? Typically 4–5 per week per platform as a baseline, scaled up for more active clients. Can you manage multiple social platforms simultaneously? Yes — we manage 3–5 platforms simultaneously with unified brand messaging.",
