        description:
          "Affiliate Marketing is a performance-based channel where you pay only for results — sales, leads, or conversions generated by your partner network. EDMA helps businesses in Indore, India, and globally build, manage, and scale affiliate programs that create an army of motivated promoters driving qualified traffic to your business 24/7.\n\nWhat We Offer: Affiliate program strategy and setup, affiliate network selection and management, partner recruitment and onboarding, commission structure design, creative asset production, affiliate tracking implementation, fraud detection, and performance reporting.\n\nBuilding Your Affiliate Network: We identify and recruit high-quality affiliates — bloggers, content creators, comparison websites, coupon portals, and niche influencers — whose audiences align perfectly with your target customer. Quality affiliates outperform quantity: we focus on recruiting partners with proven conversion track records.\n\nTracking & Attribution: We implement reliable affiliate tracking using industry-standard platforms to ensure accurate attribution, prevent commission fraud, and provide affiliates with real-time dashboards showing their performance and earnings. Transparent tracking builds trust with your affiliate partners.\n\nCommission Strategy: We design commission structures that incentivize affiliates to prioritize high-value conversions while maintaining healthy profit margins for your business. Tiered commission models, performance bonuses, and exclusive promotions keep your best affiliates motivated.\n\nCompliance & Quality Control: We monitor affiliate promotional methods to ensure brand-safe placements and compliance with advertising regulations. Our quality control prevents brand damage from unethical affiliate tactics.\n\nFAQ: How long does it take to set up an affiliate program? A basic program can launch in 2–4 weeks. What commission rates should I offer? Typical rates range from 5–30% depending on your industry and margins; we advise the optimal rate during strategy sessions.",
